name: William NEAL, Petitioner v. Sheila WOODS-SKIPPER/Commonwealth, Respondent

parties: William NEAL, Petitioner v. Sheila WOODS-SKIPPER/Commonwealth, Respondent.

opinions.text:
ORDER
PER CURIAM.
AND NOW, this 7th day of February, 2013, the Application for Leave to File Original Process is GRANTED, and the Petition for Writ of Mandamus is DENIED. Finally, the Prothonotary is directed to strike the name of the jurist from the caption.
opinions.author: PER CURIAM.

casebody.head_matter:
61 A.3d 193
William NEAL, Petitioner v. Sheila WOODS-SKIPPER/Commonwealth, Respondent.
No. 211 EM 2012.
Supreme Court of Pennsylvania.
Feb. 7, 2013.
